ry 2014, Delfina Foundation expanded into an adjacent building at 31 Catherine Place in central London, becoming London\'s largest provider of international residencies.\n\nDelfina Foundation is a non-political and non-grant-making foundation. ',NULL,0,51.4992598,'29/31 Catherine Place SW1E 6DY London',-0.140160299999934,'Delfina Foundation','See the website for further details',NULL,2,'www.delfinafoundation.com',NULL),(112,'2016-07-01 15:44:54','2016-07-01 15:44:54','28 Shad Thames SE1 2YD London','Building the world\'s leading museum of contemporary design and architecture.',NULL,0,51.5039503,'28 Shad Thames SE1 2YD London',-0.074739099999988,'Design Museum ','Monday - Sunday : 10:00 - 17:45',NULL,2,'www.designmuseum.org',NULL),(113,'2016-07-01 15:44:43','2016-07-01 15:44:43','Morley House  EC1A 2AQ London','Established in 2013 and located in Holborn, Display Gallery is focused on supporting promising emerging artists. Committed to programming exceptional multi-disciplinary shows that cultivate creative practice, the gallery established a wide network of partners and engages with meaningful contemporary critical debate. Display Gallery represents international artists and its ambitious exhibition programme has benefited from fruitful collaborations with external curators and artists. Group exhibitions compliment the solo shows and have included both established and emerging artists.',NULL,0,51.5171875,'Morley House  EC1A 2AQ London',-0.105674099999987,'Display Gallery','Tuesday - Friday : 12:00 - 18:00, Wednesday : 12:00 - 19:00, or by appointment',NULL,2,'displaygallery.co.uk',NULL),(114,'2016-07-01 15:44:43','2016-07-01 15:44:43','Enclave 5 SE8 4NT London','Contemporary Art Gallery ',NULL,0,51.4786048,'Enclave 5 SE8 4NT London',-0.0247397000000547,'Divus London ','Wednesday - Saturday : 12:00 - 18:00',NULL,2,'divus.cc/london/cs/',NULL),(115,'2016-07-01 15:44:43','2016-07-01 15:44:43','47c Streatham Hill SW2 4TS London','DOLPH is a not-for-profit visual arts group based in Streatham Hill, south London, run by two artists, Paul Cole and Natasha Kahn.\n\nDOLPH aims to engage with artists, the public and neighbouring community by staging thought-provoking exhibitions and talks that explore the vagaries and complexities of contemporary \nart practice.\n\nWe put on six exhibitions a year. Each show features a single artist. One evening during the \nshow we ask that the artist give a talk / Q&A in the space.\n\nAt DOLPH we set a brief. We ask the artists to be generous because what we are asking of \nthem is intrusive. We want them to share the personal stuff that is often only hidden away as notes to themselves, to share the idiosyncratic thoughts and influences that go on to form their later propositions. How the artist does this is up to them. They set their own terms. They are \ntheir own curators.\n\nThe Brief\n\nThe artist\'s objective is to frame an exhibition that contextualises the interests and concerns driving their practice. To share and expand upon their creative process.\n\nTheir task is to curate relevant (or contradictory) works / objects / photos / texts / music etc that have personal significance, inform and support their practice, and present them in an intriguing, cohesive exhibition.\n\nWe ask that the artist be generous in their interpretation and presentation.\n\nTheir aim is to create an exhibition that is both revealing and challenging. To conceive a show that offers a rare insight into an artist\'s creative process and affords the opportunity for greater understanding of their practice.',NULL,0,51.4405782,'47c Streatham Hill SW2 4TS London',-0.125163100000009,'DOLPH','Wednesday - Saturday : 11:00 - 17:00  or by appointment',NULL,2,'www.dolphprojects.com',NULL),(116,'2016-07-01 15:44:43','2016-07-01 15:44:43','22 Old Bond Street W1S 4PY London','Founded in 2012, Dominique Lévy represents Enrico Castellani, Frank Stella, Pierre Soulages, and Günther Uecker, as well as the Estate of Yves Klein, the Estate o