n production services, picture library/agency alongside a contemporary gallery which places an emphasis on showcasing emerging photographers, alongside new work by mid-career artists. The exhibition programme includes artist talks, panel discussions and occasional related masterclasses or workshops.\n\nAlongside the professional development and training programme, Photofusion delivers a range of crucial outreach engagement projects, working with socially and culturally marginalised young people, offering photographer-led creative programmes, skills-based accredited courses, bursaries and internships in collaboration with local organisations and a range of funding partners.',NULL,0,51.4618193,'17a Electric Lane SW9 8LA London',-0.113985200000002,'Photofusion','Monday - Saturday : 11:00 – 17:00, Thursday : 11:00 - 19:00',NULL,2,'www.photofusion.org',NULL),(298,'2016-07-01 15:44:47','2016-07-01 15:44:47','55 Eastcastle Street W1W 8EG London','Pi Artworks Istanbul/London was founded by Yesim Turanli in 1998 in Istanbul.\nBy the early 2000’s Pi Artworks was one of a small number of galleries that was successfully introducing young Turkish artists into the market. In 2008 the gallery led the way by being the first of over ten galleries to relocate to Istanbul’s Tophane district. From 2009 onwards Pi Artworks has grown to include international artists, promoting them heavily to its local market. In 2011 the gallery expanded once more by opening another branch in Istanbul, and moving its headquarters to Misir Apt. building, an historic building at the heart of Istanbul’s contemporary art district. In October 2013 it became the first Turkish commercial gallery to expand into the UK when Pi Artworks London opened on 55 Eastcastle Street, in the heart of bustling Fitzrovia. ',NULL,0,51.5164124,'55 Eastcastle Street W1W 8EG London',-0.138135700000021,'Pi Artworks','Monday - Friday : 10:00 - 18:00,  Saturday: 11:00 - 18:00',NULL,2,'www.piartworks.com',NULL),(299,'2016-07-01 15:4