ay : 13:00 – 18:00, or by appointment',NULL,2,'www.schwartzgallery.co.uk',NULL),(343,'2016-07-01 15:44:54','2016-07-01 15:44:54','Exhibition Road SW7 2DD London','Striving to be the best place in the world for people to enjoy science, the Science Museum\'s world-class collection forms an enduring record of scientific, technological and medical achievements from across the globe.',NULL,0,51.4972946,'Exhibition Road SW7 2DD London',-0.176502700000015,'Science Museum','Monday - Sunday : 10:00 - 17:15 ',NULL,2,'www.sciencemuseum.org.uk',NULL),(344,'2016-07-01 15:44:49','2016-07-01 15:44:49','171 Deptford High Street SE8 3NU London','SE8 is an independent gallery based in South-East London. Since 2009 it has worked closely with established and emerging artists in the UK and abroad, supporting them in the production and exhibition of new works and publications.',NULL,0,51.4794608,'171 Deptford High Street SE8 3NU London',-0.0264452999999776,'SE8 Gallery','Friday - Saturday : 14:00 - 18:00, or by appointment',NULL,2,'se8gallery.org',NULL),(345,'2016-07-01 15:44:49','2016-07-01 15:44:49','343 Ladbroke Grove W10 6HA London','Serena Morton was born and raised in London and came from an artistic background.\n\nFor the first ten years of her career she worked in fashion and media and then made the next logical move into the art world.\n\nSerena moved to Christie’s Auction House, King Street, London in 1994-1998 and worked in the Print Department, Modern British and Post-War and Contemporary British Paintings and Sculpture which inspired her to curate and produce contemporary art exhibitions.\n\nSerena Morton was among the first London curators of pop-up exhibitions. From 2006- 2011, she launched and directed three ‘West End’ London art galleries in Berners Street (Fitzrovia), Dover Street (Mayfair).\n\nFrom 2006-2008 Morton launched, directed and curated Ronnie Wood’s Scream Gallery in Mayfair.\n\nIn 2008 Morton started her own art gallery business. In 2010 she teamed up with music manager Raye Cosbert (Metropolis Music/Amy Winehouse manager) to open the concept art gallery Morton Metropolis.\n\nShe followed this with her own gallery, Agent Morton on Dover Street. After a year curating and establishing a contemporary art exhibition for the private members club Home House on Portman Square, she built and launched Serena Morton gallery at Canalside, 385 Ladbroke Grove. In November 2014 she consolidated her position in the area by opening her second space, at 343 Ladbroke Grove.\n\nSerena Morton’s exhibitions have won critical approval and have a proven track record of identifying emerging artists. Serena Morton supports and advises artists and collectors on all areas of the art world.',NULL,0,51.5232443,'343 Ladbroke Grove W10 6HA London',-0.213738299999932,'Serena Morton','Monday - Friday : 10:00 - 18:00, Saturday :11:00 - 16:00',NULL,2,'www.serenamorton.com',NULL),(346,'2016-07-01 15:44:49','2016-07-01 15:44:49','Kensington Gardens W2 3XA London','Championing new ideas in contemporary art since it opened in 1970, the Serpentine has presented pioneering exhibitions of 2,263 artists over 45 years, showing a wide range of work from emerging practitioners to the most internationally recognised artists and architects of our time. ',NULL,0,51.5047891,'Kensington Gardens W2 3XA London',-0.175007499999992,'Serpentine Gallery','Monday - Sunday : 10:00 - 18:00',NULL,2,'www.serpentinegallery.org',NULL),(347,'2016-07-01 15:44:49','2016-07-01 15:44:49','West Carriage Drive W2 2AR London','Championing new ideas in contemporary art since it opened in 1970, the Serpentine has presented pioneering exhibitions of 2,263 artists over 45 years, showing a wide range of work from emerging practitioners to the most internationally recognised artists and architects of our time. ',NULL,0,51.5070098,'West Carriage Drive W2 2AR London',-0.171517999999992,'Serpentine Sackler Gallery','Tuesday - Sunday : 10:00 - 18:00 ',NULL,2,'www.serpentinegallery.org',NULL),(348,'2